Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian using the word "mleka" in different forms and positions:

1. *Mleka* ima u frižideru. (There is milk in the fridge.)
2. Da li si video koliko je *mleka* u ovom pakovanju? (Have you seen how much milk is in this package?)
3. Nisam siguran da li mi je dovoljno *mleka* za kafu. (I'm not sure if I have enough milk for my coffee.)
4. Jeste li ikada probali *mleko* sa medom? (Have you ever tried milk with honey?)
5. Njegova omiljena poslastica su palačinke sa puno *mleka*. (His favorite treat is pancakes with lots of milk.)
6. Kupila sam danas dva *litra mleka*. (I bought two liters of milk today.)
7. *Mleko* se prodaje po povoljnoj ceni ovog meseca. (Milk is being sold at a favorable price this month.)
8. Ona ne može da pije *mleko* jer je intolerantna na laktozu. (She can't drink milk because she's lactose intolerant.)

*Note: The word "mleka" is highlighted with a star in each sentence for clarity. The translations of each sentence are provided in parentheses.*